## ContextTopBar

**Path**: `@/components/ContextTopBar`  
**Figma**: Roy design system → top nav bar, types=Shopping (node 496:658).

Contextual top bar: back button + section label on the left; center title; filter and search icon buttons on the right. White background, bottom border. Padding 16px 24px, height 80px, gap 16px. Back label: medium/paragraph-sm (14px, #101828). Title: semi/body-md (16px, #121412). Back and action icons 24px and 20px in 40×40 hit areas.

**Props**

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
|------|------|----------|-------------|
| `backLabel` | `string` | Yes | Label next to back (e.g. "Section", "Categories") |
| `title` | `string` | Yes | Center title (e.g. "Perch") |
| `onBack` | `() => void` | No | Called when back is pressed |
| `onFilter` | `() => void` | No | Called when filter is pressed |
| `onSearch` | `() => void` | No | Called when search is pressed |
| `className` | `string` | No | Applied to the root `<header>` |

**Exports**: `ContextTopBar`, `ContextTopBarProps`.

**Example**

```tsx
import { ContextTopBar } from "@/components/ContextTopBar";

<ContextTopBar
  backLabel="Section"
  title="Perch"
  onBack={() => router.back()}
  onFilter={() => openFilters()}
  onSearch={() => openSearch()}
/>
```

